name: RestoreAgentRequest
description:
The request message for [Agents.RestoreAgent][google.cloud.dialogflow.v2.Agents.RestoreAgent].

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.dialogflow.v2.RestoreAgentRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. The project that the agent to restore is associated with. Format: projects/<Project ID>.

params.name: data.agent_uri
params.description: The URI to a Google Cloud Storage file containing the agent to restore. Note: The URI must start with "gs://".

params.name: data.agent_content
params.description:
The agent to restore. Example for how to restore an agent via the command line: 

curl \ 'https://dialogflow.googleapis.com/v2/projects/<project_name>/agent:restore\ -X POST \ -H 'Authorization: Bearer '$(gcloud auth application-default print-access-token) \ -H 'Accept: application/json' \ -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \ --compressed \ --data-binary "{ 'agentContent': '$(cat <agent zip file> | base64 -w 0)' }"
